// ERROR: E2450
// Rewritten 2026-07-18 (P0 borrowck-nll-foundation, ADR-0046 unfrozen).
// OLD shape: `let r = &0 x; return x;` where `x: Integer` was a PARAMETER
// and `r` was never read again. That was an OVER-REFUSE, not a real bug:
// under real NLL a reference's loan ends at its own last use — since `r`
// had none, the loan was already dead by the time `x` moved out via
// `return x`. The pre-P0 checker mis-classified `Statement::Drop` on a
// REFERENCE local as a genuine read (liveness.rs), which pinned `r` "live"
// through scope exit regardless of real usage, plus the lowerer's
// source-drops-before-dest ordering for `flush_all_for_return` — together
// these coincidentally produced E2450 here for the WRONG reason.
//
// Rewritten below to a genuine gap: the borrow escapes its owner's scope
// (owner `x` dies at the end of the inner block) and IS read afterward —
// real dangling reference, must still fire E2450 post-fix.
function demo() -> Integer {
    let r = {
        let x = "hello"
        &0 x
    }
    return length(r)
}
function main() -> Integer {
    return demo()
}
